## Overview
Smart Lender is a practical, production-oriented loan decision assistant. This Epic documents what we collected, why it matters for model development, and how the project structure supports reproducible ML engineering. The text below explains decisions in plain language and highlights what an engineer or reviewer will need to reproduce the results.

Summary:

- We collected a single, well-structured loan application dataset that contains the features needed to predict approval outcomes. The dataset is stored under `DATASET/` so raw data remains separate from code and artifacts.
- The architecture favors separation of concerns: user interface and runtime code live under `Flask/`, while development assets (notebooks, experiments) remain under `Training/`. This reduces accidental coupling between research and production code.
- This deliverable is intentionally specific: it lists file names, the schema, and exactly what was verified so a reviewer can re-run the verification steps without ambiguity.

---

